definition: variant of 怎麼|怎么[zen3 me5]
suffix, used to form interrogative 什麼|什么[shen2 me5], what?, indefinite 這麼|这么[zhe4 me5] thus, etc
how?/how about?/how was it?/how are things?
not up to much/very indifferent/nothing great about it/nothing good to be said about it
how can this be?/what's to be done?/what an awful mess!
variant of 怎麼了|怎么了[zen3 me5 le5]
what's the matter?/what's going on?/how could that be?/how did that come about?/what's it all about?
How did it happen?/What's wrong?/What went wrong?/What's up?
variant of 怎麼了|怎么了[zen3 me5 le5]

sentences.english: And i have no idea how the hell you get the impressions that Okinawans are pro-Chinese.
sentences.chinese: 我不知道你怎么会有冲绳县民亲华的印象。

sentences.english: So, combustible ice is how come from?
sentences.chinese: 那么，可燃冰是怎么来的呢？

sentences.english: How about tidying up a bit in the sitting-room ?
sentences.chinese: 把起居室稍微打扫一下怎么样？

sentences.english: How do you really know what goes into store-bought baby food?
sentences.chinese: 你怎么真的知道什么进店买婴儿食品呢？

sentences.english: This time on the need to install streetlights, but also how streetlight control?
sentences.chinese: 这个时候就需要安装路灯，可是路灯又要怎么控制？

sentences.english: I hope I don't need it, because I don't even know how to load it.
sentences.chinese: 我希望我并不需要它，因为我还不知道怎么装子弹呢。

sentences.english: What do you think about Union Square?
sentences.chinese: 你觉得联合广场怎么样？

sentences.english: And how would you deal with this brigand?
sentences.chinese: 那你要怎么对付这个土匪呢？

sentences.english: However some grownup parents never figure out how to talk to a child.
sentences.chinese: 然而，许多家长怎么也学不会正确地和孩子交谈。

sentences.english: I have a job interview in an hour and none of it is coming off.
sentences.chinese: 我一个小时以后要去面试，这些玩意怎么也洗不掉。

sentences.english: No one could account for the fact that one of the boxes was extremely heavy.
sentences.chinese: 此中有只箱子特别重，可谁也弄不清是怎么回事。

sentences.english: That's good. I was just wondering about how to spend my free time on weekends.
sentences.chinese: 太好了，我正在想怎么打发我的周末时间呢？

sentences.english: What do you think about the two-party system in the United States?
sentences.chinese: 你认为美国的两党制怎么样？

sentences.english: It's not like we're back in Ontario, how's that?
sentences.chinese: 这不像是回到了安大略湖，怎么会？

sentences.english: Without you deny yourself, think about what other people live.
sentences.chinese: 不要自我否定，想想其他人是怎么过的。

definition: dialectal equivalent of 怎麼|怎么[zen3 me5]
dialectal equivalent of 為什麼|为什么[wei4 shen2 me5]
how?/how about?/how was it?/how are things?

particle indicating that a previously asked question is to be applied to the preceding word ("What about ...?", "And ...?")/particle for inquiring about location ("Where is ...?")/particle signaling a pause, to emphasize the preceding words and allow the listener time to take them on board ("ok?", "are you with me?")/(at the end of a declarative sentence) particle indicating continuation of a state or action/particle indicating strong affirmation
is or isn't/yes or no/whether or not
dialectal equivalent of 什麼|什么[shen2 me5]/also pr. [sha4]
youngest/most junior/tiny/one (unambiguous spoken form when spelling out numbers, esp. on telephone or in military)/one or ace on dice or dominoes/variant of 吆[yao1], to shout
so much/this much/how much?/this way/like this
(particle equivalent to 啊 after a vowel, expressing surprise or doubt)
interjection or grunt of agreement/uhm/Ah, OK/expression of recognition/Oh, it's you!
modal particle ending sentence, showing affirmation, approval, or consent
interjection expressing doubt or requiring answer/Eh?/what?
interjection of surprise or doubt/Eh?/My!/what's up?
